{
  "texts": [
    "Perceval users may send jobs consisting in photonic circuits, or a gate-based circuit (GB) or a unitary matrix (U), along with the desired input state to the Quandela Cloud.",
    "The job is first processed by a CPU, which computes the necessary phase shifts ⃗ ϕ to apply, and subsequently the voltages ⃗ V for the on-chip phase shifters from our compilation and transpilation process.",
    "Finally, the user receives the collected single-photon and coincidence counts after the computation on the quantum processing unit (QPU).",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41566-024-01403-4 manuscript in preparation).",
    "Our method exploits symmetries so that the contribution of most F ψ s to F avg cancel out, allowing F avg to be expressed as a finite discrete sum F avg = ∑ K i=1 w i m i of K expectation values m i with weight w i (see Supplementary Section 5)."
  ]
}